# Verification evidence (Verification Evidence)

> Stored in `.harness/loops/specs/<task-name>/evidence.md`. Used to record objective evidence that a single change or deployment succeeded. Without evidence, the state must not be set to DONE.

## 1. Automated verification results

- **CI/CD log screenshot or link**: `[paste the link showing all pipeline stages green]`
- **Smoke test results**: `[if you ran curl or a health check script, paste the 200 OK response]`

## 2. Observability dashboard metrics (Monitoring Metrics)

- **Pre-release core metric baseline**: `[e.g., before release CPU was at 30%, 5xx error rate 0%]`
- **Post-release 10-minute observation window metrics**: `[e.g., after release CPU is at 32%, 5xx error rate remains 0%]`
- **Conclusion**: all metrics are stable, no alert thresholds triggered.

## 3. Spot checks

- `[If a manual page visit is needed to confirm JS is not broken, record "visited the main site, page loaded normally"]`
- `[If the DB schema was changed, record "verified via DB console that the new field's default value is populated correctly"]`
